A 69-YEAR-OLD lion owner has been killed by his two lions at Hoedspruit, Mopani district in Limpopo. Police spokesman Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said it’s alleged that the owner could have been killed by two of his lions. He said it’s believed that the two lionesses attacked the man during one of their usual walks. The incident allegedly took place while his wife was helplessly watching. The police and emergency services were called and on arrival, the man was found with multiple injuries. He was declared dead on the scene. The lionesses have since been moved to another game lodge in the area. The dead man was identified as Arthur Mathewson. Limpopo police commissioner Lieutenant-General Nneke Ledwaba has warned residents, especially animal owners, to be careful around dangerous animals.